<P>And as they &s;ee Truth, and Holine&s;s, and Goodne&s;s in their wonderful Glory, and Beauty; &s;o al&s;o Folly, and Fal&s;hood, and Sin, in its wonderful ugline&s;s and deformi|ty. Sin <HI>appears to be &s;in,</HI> to them, <HI>Rom.</HI> 7. Folly to be folly, fal&s;hood to be fal&s;hood; they &s;ee men as men, Chri&s;t as Chri&s;t, Truth as Truth, Holine&s;s as Holine&s;s; and they &s;ee Bea&s;ts as Bea&s;ts, Fools as Fools, Sin as Sin, Devils as Devils, Hell as Hell: They &s;ee all things as they are, Temptations as they are, Delu&s;ions as they are; they &s;ee what is under them, the Hook under the bait, the &s;ting in the Locu&s;ts Tail, the war in the Devils heart, carried on under his fawning face; <HI>We are not ignorant of his Devices.</HI></P>
